# Example of ~/.zshrc.local — copy to ~/.zshrc.local on the machine that needs it.
# Sourced at the very end of ~/.zshrc, so anything here overrides committed config.
#
# Use this file for things that shouldn't be committed:
#   - Secrets / tokens
#   - Machine-specific PATH additions
#   - Per-machine env vars (e.g. AWS_PROFILE)
#   - Aliases that only make sense on one machine

# --- PATH additions -----------------------------------------------
# export PATH="$HOME/.local/bin:$PATH"

# --- Environment --------------------------------------------------
# export EDITOR="code --wait"
# export AWS_PROFILE="work"
# export OPENAI_API_KEY="sk-..."

# --- Machine-specific aliases -------------------------------------
# alias work='cd ~/ujet'

# --- Tool init that only applies to this machine ------------------
# eval "$(direnv hook zsh)"
